  "body": "#### System information\n\n```\nVersion: 1.5.0-unstable-c8a8ad97\nProtocol Versions: [63 62 61]\nNetwork Id: 1\nGo Version: go1.6.2\nOS: darwin\n```\n\nI'm attempting to use `eth_subscribe` + `logs` with websockets and/or ipc, and I'm noticing it happily sends the events along for a while, but eventually stops receiving subscription messages (usually after a few minutes). The websocket connection seems to still be open as I still receive responses for other requests.\n\nMy subscription request looks like this:\n\n```\n{\n    \"id\": 1,\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n    \"method\": \"eth_subscribe\",\n    \"params\": [\"logs\", {\n        \"address\": \"0xea3fc35beafe2dff9efa562b903f4695c26a60dc\",\n        \"topics\": [\"0x63f140d7adcc464732c9379020aa9e5ce1b1e350796814d780ea3ca41d62a36b\"]\n    }]\n}\n```\n\nI establish a websocket connection, and then have a script that triggers the log on the contract (https://github.com/AugurProject/augur-core/blob/master/src/functions/createMarket.se#L174) every 30 seconds or so. If I kill my websocket connection and resend the `eth_subscribe`, the subscription messages (temporarily) come back.\n",
